---
// Security & Data Residency page (scope: onprem). Highest claim-risk page.
//
// Structure (SPEC.md Security map):
//   1. Hero: states the cloud-AI exposure plainly.
//   2. Jurisdiction diagram: teal on-prem boundary with zero outbound arrows
//      vs a red without-Hive external-cloud path. Rendered as a labelled
//      figure, NOT a ChartFrame: this is an architectural diagram, not a data
//      chart, so it must not carry a data-source citation.
//   3. Two exposure vectors: US CLOUD Act + litigation discovery, with the
//      exact generic court sentence (no date, no case, no provider name).
//   4. How Hive removes the exposure.
//   5. Designed-for controls, not certifications.
//   6. Honest Hive Cloud scope boundary.
//   7. Verbatim security disclaimer (names S Cubed).
//   8. Closing CTA.
//
// Claim guardrail: never assert a framework is satisfied or accredited;
// sovereignty stays on-prem scoped and qualified in the same sentence; no cost
// proof and no named-vendor cost story belong on this page. Legal and
// regulatory statements are wrapped in <Claim id> tied to the matching
// sources[].claim_id in security.mdx (the compliance source of record).
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Claim from '../components/Claim.astro';
import JurisdictionDiagram from '../components/charts/JurisdictionDiagram.astro';

const eyebrow = 'Security and data residency';
---

<Base
  title="Security & Data Residency"
  description="Designed for on-prem data residency. Open model weights run entirely on your hardware; inference never calls an external API."
>
  {/* 1. HERO (state the exposure plainly). */}
  <section class="shell py-section hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">{eyebrow}</p>
    <h1>Your data does not leave your building.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Cloud AI works by sending your prompts, your documents, and your
      customers' information to a provider you do not control. Hive runs the
      model on your own hardware instead. Self-hosted deployment: your hardware,
      your network, your data.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="cta cta--primary tap-target" href="/book-a-demo">Book a Demo</a>
      <a class="cta cta--ghost tap-target" href="#how-hive-removes-it">
        See how it works
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* 2. JURISDICTION DIAGRAM (architectural diagram, no data citation). */}
  <section class="band">
    <div class="shell py-section">
      <p class="eyebrow">Where your data goes</p>
      <h2>Two architectures. One leaves your building.</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        With Hive on-prem, open model weights run entirely on your hardware and
        inference never calls an external API. Without Hive, every request
        travels to an external cloud service that sits under a foreign
        jurisdiction.
      </p>

      <figure class="diagram">
        <JurisdictionDiagram
          ariaLabel="On the left, a teal boundary labelled your network boundary contains your data and the model with no outbound arrows. On the right, a red path shows your data leaving your network to an external cloud AI service under foreign jurisdiction."
        />
        <figcaption class="diagram__reading">
          On the left, every inference stays inside your network boundary. On
          the right, your data leaves your network the moment a cloud AI service
          answers a request.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* 3. TWO EXPOSURE VECTORS (CLOUD Act + litigation discovery). */}
  <section class="shell py-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">What you are exposed to</p>
    <h2>Two ways your data becomes someone else's to reach.</h2>
    <p class="intro">
      Once your data leaves your network, there are two distinct ways it becomes
      reachable by someone other than you.
    </p>

    <div class="vectors">
      <article class="vector-card">
        <h3 class="vector-card__title">Government compulsion</h3>
        <p>
          <Claim id="cloud-act-extraterritorial">The US CLOUD Act lets US
          authorities compel a US-owned provider to hand over data it holds or
          controls, regardless of where that data is physically stored.</Claim>
        </p>
        <p class="vector-card__note">
          A data centre in your own country does not remove this exposure when
          the operator is US-owned.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="vector-card">
        <h3 class="vector-card__title">Litigation discovery</h3>
        <p>
          <Claim id="litigation-discovery">In a legal dispute, a court can order
          a provider to produce the electronically stored information it holds
          about you.</Claim>
        </p>
        <p class="vector-card__note">
          Data you handed to a third party can be pulled into a matter you are
          not even a party to.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="court-line">
      <Claim id="court-preserve-logs">A US court has already ordered a major AI
      provider to preserve chat logs.</Claim>
    </p>
  </section>

  {/* 4. HOW HIVE REMOVES IT. */}
  <section id="how-hive-removes-it" class="band">
    <div class="shell py-section">
      <p class="eyebrow">How Hive removes it</p>
      <h2>There is no provider to compel, because the provider is you.</h2>
      <ul class="removes">
        <li>Open model weights run entirely on your hardware.</li>
        <li>Every inference executes locally.</li>
        <li>
          No prompt, no response, and no document ever calls an external API or
          leaves your network boundary.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* 5. DESIGNED-FOR CONTROLS, NOT CERTIFICATIONS. */}
  <section class="shell py-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Designed-for controls, not certifications</p>
    <h2>Not a compliance certification. A control architecture you can audit.</h2>
    <p class="intro">
      Hive is designed for on-prem data residency, and customers validate
      regulatory fit with their own counsel. The controls are architectural
      facts you can inspect, not badges we claim.
    </p>
    <ul class="controls">
      <li>The model runs inside your network.</li>
      <li>The inference path has no outbound call.</li>
      <li>You hold the hardware, the keys, and the logs.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  {/* 6. HONEST HIVE CLOUD SCOPE BOUNDARY. */}
  <section class="band">
    <div class="shell py-section">
      <p class="eyebrow">Hive Cloud is different</p>
      <h2>We say the boundary plainly.</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Hive Cloud runs on third-party infrastructure. It does not carry the
        same data-residency properties as the on-prem edition. If your
        requirement is that data stays on hardware you control, the on-prem
        edition is the one that meets it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* 7. SECURITY DISCLAIMER (verbatim, names S Cubed). */}
  <section class="shell py-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Disclaimer</p>
    <p class="disclaimer" role="note">
      Hive's on-prem deployment is designed so that your data does not leave
      your infrastructure. This is an architectural property, not a compliance
      certification. Whether this architecture satisfies your organisation's
      obligations under PIPEDA, HIPAA, or other frameworks is a determination
      your team must make with qualified legal counsel. S Cubed does not provide
      legal or compliance advice.
    </p>
  </section>

  {/* 8. CLOSING CTA. */}
  <section class="band">
    <div class="shell py-section closing">
      <h2>See it run inside your own network.</h2>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="cta cta--primary tap-target" href="/book-a-demo">Book a Demo</a>
        <a class="cta cta--ghost tap-target" href="/pricing">See Pricing</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Shared eyebrow (team-aligned: mirrors Footer geo-label). */
  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--text-faint);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }

  /* Alternating full-bleed band on a raised surface. */
  .band {
    background-color: var(--bg-raised);
    border-block: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 30px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .lede {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin: 20px 0 0;
  }

  .intro {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 68ch;
    margin: 16px 0 0;
  }

  /* CTA recipe (team-aligned). Primary = gold pill (Nav .nav__cta). */
  .cta-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  .cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 15px;
    padding: 10px 18px;
    border-radius: 10px;
  }

  .cta--primary {
    background-color: var(--gold);
    color: #1a1205;
  }

  .cta--primary:hover {
    filter: brightness(1.05);
  }

  .cta--ghost {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
    color: var(--text);
    background-color: transparent;
  }

  .cta--ghost:hover {
    border-color: var(--text-faint);
  }

  /* Jurisdiction diagram figure. */
  .diagram {
    margin: 32px 0 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background-color: var(--bg-card);
    padding: 28px;
  }

  .diagram :global(svg) {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .diagram__reading {
    margin: 16px 0 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Exposure-vector cards. Risk framing = red left accent. */
  .vectors {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  .vector-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--red);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background-color: var(--bg-card);
    padding: 24px;
  }

  .vector-card__title {
    font-size: 17px;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }

  .vector-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .vector-card__note {
    margin-top: 12px !important;
    color: var(--text-muted) !important;
    font-size: 14px !important;
  }

  .court-line {
    margin: 28px 0 0;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  /* Safe / control lists. Teal marker = sovereign / safe. */
  .removes,
  .controls {
    margin: 24px 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 14px;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .removes li,
  .controls li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 28px;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .removes li::before,
  .controls li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.45em;
    width: 12px;
    height: 12px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background-color: var(--teal);
  }

  /* Verbatim disclaimer block. */
  .disclaimer {
    margin: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background-color: var(--bg-card);
    padding: 24px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 78ch;
  }

  .closing {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .closing .cta-row {
    justify-content: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .vectors {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    h2 {
      font-size: 26px;
    }
  }
</style>
